data.text:
BJORK John W., born April 18, 1929 in Eureka, S.D. to Art and Grace Bjork. He died Sept. 3, 1995 in Oklahoma City after a brief courageous battle with brain cancer. John graduated from the University of Minnesota in 1951 and the University of Washington in 1953. He served in the U.S. Army from 1953 to 1957. John was a Social Worker for the Indian Health Service in Flandreau, S.D., Aberdeen, S.D. and Oklahoma City, Ok. and retired in 1985 after 31 years of service. His lifelong special interest was in all aspects of the former Milwaukee Road Railroad. Survivors include his wife, Barbara; daughters and sons-in-law, Lynn and Perry Phillips, Sheboygan, Wi., Beth and Ron Wann, OKC, Ok. and Amy and Rick Skeels, Reno, Nv.; grandchildren, Patrick, Parker and Katherine Phillips, Carson and Kyle Wann; sister, Jean Branstiter, Bellingham, Wa.; and brother, Roy Bjork, Sioux City, Ia. Memorial service will be 10:00 a.m. Thursday, September 7, 1995 at Hahn-Cook/Street & Draper Chapel. In lieu of flowers, the family requests donations be given to the following: The Milwaukee Road Historical Assoc., PO Box 44576, Madison, Wi. 53744 or The Saint Paul Chamber of Orchestra, Landmark Center, 75 West Fifth Street, Saint Paul, Mn. 55102 BIOG: NAME:
